         <abstract>
            <p>A concise analytical framework for quantifying the relationships between financial leverage and other determinants of the return to equity is presented. The model analyzes changes in leverage, return on total assets, tax rate, and interest rate, and relates them to changes in the return to equity. The rigorous analytical framework is addressed primarily to academics, while the detailed numerical illustrations provide applications for the executive.</p>
         </abstract>
